President Obama called President Calderon of Mexico to express his shock and sadness over the tragic death of Mexican Interior Secretary Francisco Blake Mora and seven other Mexican government officials in a helicopter crash. He offered his thoughts and prayers to the families of the victims, President Calderon, and the Mexican people. The United States deeply regrets the loss of these officials, who were close partners and strong public servants for Mexico. President Obama reaffirmed the close partnership between the United States and Mexico and pledged to provide any assistance needed in the future.